"831","SUB-ITEM 77E - LEGAL PROCEEDINGS"
"832","Since October 2003,"
"833","Federated and related"
"834"," entities (collectively,"
"835","Federated) and various"
"836","Federated-sponsored"
"837","mutual funds (Funds)"
"838","have been named as defendants"
"839","in several class action"
"840","lawsuits now pending"
"841","in the United States"
"842","District Court for the"
"843","District of Maryland."
"844","The lawsuits were"
"845","purportedly filed on"
"846","behalf of people who"
"847","purchased, owned"
"848","and/or redeemed"
"849","shares of certain Funds"
"850","during specified"
"851","periods beginning"
"852","November 1, 1998. The suits"
"853","are generally similar in"
"854","alleging that"
"855","Federated engaged in illegal"
"856","and improper trading practices"
"857","including market timing and"
"858","late trading in"
"859","concert with certain"
"860","institutional traders,"
"861","which allegedly caused"
"862","financial injury to the mutual"
"863","fund"
"864","shareholders. Federated"
"865","without admitting the validity"
"866","of any claim has reached a"
"867","preliminary settlement"
"868","with the Plaintiffs in these"
"869","cases. Any settlement would"
"870","have to be approved by the Court."
"871","     Federated entities have"
"872","also been named as defendants"
"873","in several additional lawsuits"
"874","that are now"
"875","pending in the United States"
"876","District Court for the Western"
"877","District of Pennsylvania. These"
"878","lawsuits have"
"879","been consolidated into a single"
"880","action alleging excessive"
"881","advisory fees involving one"
"882","of the Funds."
"883","     The Board of the Funds"
"884","retained the law firm of Dickstein"
"885","Shapiro LLP to represent the Funds in"
"886","each of the lawsuits described"
"887"," in the preceding two paragraphs."
"888"," Federated and the Funds, and their"
"889","respective counsel, have been"
"890","defending this litigation, and"
"891","none of the Funds remains a"
"892","defendant in"
"893","any of the lawsuits. Additional"
"894","lawsuits based upon similar allegations"
"895"," may"
"896","be filed in the future. The"
"897","potential impact of these lawsuits,"
"898","all of which seek monetary damages,"
"899","attorneys' fees and expenses,"
"900","and future potential similar suits is"
"901","uncertain. Although we do not believe"
"902","that these lawsuits will have a"
"903","material adverse effect on the Funds,"
"904","there can be no assurance that these"
"905","suits, ongoing adverse"
"906","publicity and/or other developments"
"907","resulting from the allegations in"
"908"," these matters will not result in"
"909","increased redemptions, or reduced"
"910","sales of shares of the Funds or"
"911","other adverse consequences for the"
"912","Funds."
